<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Helvetica, sans-serif">
Crusader,<P>It's useful in ANY situation where we have a hard time tanking the mob(s).  For example, 6 Hibbie guards, maybe 10 players, mez gone.  Spread out, confuse confuse confuse nuke like crazy.  You're going to tell me it doesn't work?  I've done it and it saved our asses one night.  The guards were on the healers hard and it absolutely worked.  Amnesia wasn't the ticket since we didn't have enough tanks at the moment (damn Middies attacking the rear at the same time).  It was better before, but it's still useful now, used properly that is.<P>As for my 41+ comment I was under the impression that the "attacking allies" code only kicked in on the 41 and 48 versions of the spell.  If it used to work on a lower level version too I stand corrected.<P>As for "promises to the client" Magwa is right, but BFD.  Game companies speak in code and "a few days" unfortunately rarely translates to "a few days."  Where do you want this "magical" post to go?  The Pendragon boards?  The devs frequently don't listen to the TLs.  The Vault?  You can do that yourself.  Our big problem is we really don't know how to reach the devs with our problems.  Putatively the Pendragon board is the way to go, but Bullseye has posted numerous times that the devs do not listen much of the time.  So it seems rather pointless to build up moral outrage over a relatively minor (and hopefully somewhat temporary) nerf.
