<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Helvetica, sans-serif">
Everyone is certainly entitled to their own opinions, and let me give you mine in a bit more detail:<P>In the grand scheme of things in this game (ie. look at the big pic and not just our Sorc issues) the change to Confusion is pretty minor compared to all of the other changes we've seen made in the last few months.  It affects us a lot more in PvE than PvP, and, in the grand scheme of things PvP changes are a hell of a lot more important than PvE.  It's minor because it still works, just not as well, nor as completely, as it used to.  It's minor because hopefully they'll keep their word and make it temporary.  But, all that said <B>it is STILL a useful spell!</B>  For the record I'll state again I think it was a poor decision on their part, but Mythic is apparently like Verant in that they don't like it when their "special mobs" are killed easily.<P>I agree that it's a nerf, but completely disagree with the severity of the nerf and the typical reaction from many of this board.  Frankly, this place is becoming a big negative feedback loop.  As many of you have I too have managed to level up (49.1 at the moment) and will have no problem hitting 50.  With all the nerfs I'm still viable and am sought after for both PvE and PvP groups.  I'm still able to have a positive impact on groups in both PvE and PvP.  Sure, I'd like Mythic to get a clue when it comes to Sorcs, but I've discovered I have damned little say in what decisions they make.  So I personally prefer to roll with the punches (sometimes it takes a while to roll =P) as much as possible instead of giving myself heartburn over decisions I have 0 influence over.<P>Your own mileage, however, may vary.
</FONT>
